Description: Fix black screens for beat 0/2/4 (Core Profile texture 0)
 In OpenGL Core Profile, texture name 0 is not a valid texture object.
 The original GLX code did not explicitly request a core profile context
 (GLX_CONTEXT_PROFILE_MASK_ARB was absent), so the driver could hand out
 a Compatibility Profile context where texture 0 is the well-defined
 "default texture" (returns (0,0,0,0) when sampled).
 .
 The SDL2 port explicitly requests SDL_GL_CONTEXT_PROFILE_CORE.  In core
 profile, binding texture name 0 to a sampler is undefined behaviour.
 Many drivers return (0,0,0,1) — alpha=1 — which the post.fs shader
 interprets as a fully-opaque logo, covering the entire scene with a
 black rectangle for approximately half the hard-scene duration
 (every time beat == 0, 2 or 4, i.e. roughly every 0.87 s).
 .
 Fix: create a 1x1 RGBA(0,0,0,0) "notex" texture in initAntagonism()
 and use it as the "no overlay" placeholder wherever texture 0 was bound.
 The alpha=0 value is still interpreted as "no logo" by the shader, but
 the texture object is now valid in both Compatibility and Core profiles.
